{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Jer|27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","chapter":27,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":1,"text":"At the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah son of Josiah, king of Judah, this word came to Jeremiah from the Lord:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":2,"text":"This is what the Lord said to me: “Make chains and yoke bars for yourself and put them on your neck.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":3,"text":"Send word to the king of Edom, the king of Moab, the king of the Ammonites, the king of Tyre, and the king of Sidon through messengers who are coming to King Zedekiah of Judah in Jerusalem.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":4,"text":"Command them to go to their masters, saying, ‘This is what the Lord of Armies, the God of Israel, says: Tell this to your masters:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":5,"text":"“By my great strength and outstretched arm, I made the earth, and the people, and animals on the face of the earth. I give it to anyone I please.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":6,"text":"So now I have placed all these lands under the authority of my servant Nebuchadnezzar, king of Babylon. I have even given him the wild animals to serve him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":7,"text":"All nations will serve him, his son, and his grandson until the time for his own land comes, and then many nations and great kings will enslave him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":8,"text":"“ ‘ “As for the nation or kingdom that does not serve King Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon and does not place its neck under the yoke of the king of Babylon, that nation I will punish by sword, famine, and plague —this is the Lord’s declaration —until through him I have destroyed it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":9,"text":"So you should not listen to your prophets, diviners, dreamers, fortune-tellers, or sorcerers who say to you, ‘Don’t serve the king of Babylon!’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":10,"text":"They are prophesying a lie to you so that you will be removed from your land. I will banish you, and you will perish.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":11,"text":"But as for the nation that will put its neck under the yoke of the king of Babylon and serve him, I will leave it in its own land, and that nation will cultivate it and reside in it. This is the Lord’s declaration.”’”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":12,"text":"I spoke to King Zedekiah of Judah in the same way: “Put your necks under the yoke of the king of Babylon, serve him and his people, and live!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":13,"text":"Why should you and your people die by the sword, famine, and plague as the Lord has threatened against any nation that does not serve the king of Babylon?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":14,"text":"Do not listen to the words of the prophets who are telling you, ‘Don’t serve the king of Babylon,’ for they are prophesying a lie to you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":15,"text":"‘I have not sent them’ —this is the Lord’s declaration —‘and they are prophesying falsely in my name; therefore, I will banish you, and you will perish —you and the prophets who are prophesying to you.’”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":16,"text":"Then I spoke to the priests and all these people, saying, “This is what the Lord says: ‘Do not listen to the words of your prophets. They are prophesying to you, claiming, “Look, very soon now the articles of the Lord’s temple will be brought back from Babylon.” They are prophesying a lie to you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":17,"text":"Do not listen to them. Serve the king of Babylon and live! Why should this city become a ruin?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":18,"text":"If they are indeed prophets and if the word of the Lord is with them, let them intercede with the Lord of Armies not to let the articles that remain in the Lord’s temple, in the palace of the king of Judah, and in Jerusalem go to Babylon.’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":19,"text":"For this is what the Lord of Armies says about the pillars, the basin, the water carts, and the rest of the articles that still remain in this city,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":20,"text":"those King Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon did not take when he deported Jeconiah son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, from Jerusalem to Babylon along with all the nobles of Judah and Jerusalem.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":21,"text":"Yes, this is what the Lord of Armies, the God of Israel, says about the articles that remain in the temple of the Lord, in the palace of the king of Judah, and in Jerusalem:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":27,"verse":22,"text":"‘They will be taken to Babylon and will remain there until I attend to them again.’ This is the Lord’s declaration. ‘Then I will bring them up and restore them to this place.’”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","chapter":27,"paragraphStarts":[1,8,12,16],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"The Yoke of Babylon"},{"beforeVerse":12,"text":"Warning to Zedekiah"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"At the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Some Hb mss, Syr, Arabic; other Hb mss, DSS read Jehoiakim"},{"kind":"text","text":" son of Josiah, king of Judah, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 24:17","book":"2Ki","chapter":24,"verse":17,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 1:3","book":"Jer","chapter":1,"verse":3,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 21:1","book":"Jer","chapter":21,"verse":1,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" this word came to Jeremiah from the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"LXX omits this v."},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 24:17","book":"2Ki","chapter":24,"verse":17},{"label":"Jr 1:3","book":"Jer","chapter":1,"verse":3},{"label":"Jr 21:1","book":"Jer","chapter":21,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Some Hb mss, Syr, Arabic; other Hb mss, DSS read Jehoiakim"},{"marker":2,"text":"LXX omits this v."}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"This is what the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" said to me: “Make chains and yoke bars "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 28:10–13","book":"Jer","chapter":28,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" for yourself and put them on your neck. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 2:20","book":"Jer","chapter":2,"verse":20,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 5:5","book":"Jer","chapter":5,"verse":5,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 30:8","book":"Jer","chapter":30,"verse":8,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jr 28:10–13","book":"Jer","chapter":28,"verse":10},{"label":"Jr 2:20","book":"Jer","chapter":2,"verse":20},{"label":"Jr 5:5","book":"Jer","chapter":5,"verse":5},{"label":"Jr 30:8","book":"Jer","chapter":30,"verse":8}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Send word to the king of Edom, the king of Moab, the king of the Ammonites, the king of Tyre, and the king of Sidon "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 25:21–22","book":"Jer","chapter":25,"verse":21,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" through messengers who are coming to King Zedekiah of Judah in Jerusalem. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jr 25:21–22","book":"Jer","chapter":25,"verse":21}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Command them to go to their masters, saying, ‘This is what the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" of Armies, the God of Israel, says: Tell this to your masters: "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“By my great strength and outstretched arm, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 4:34","book":"Deu","chapter":4,"verse":34,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 5:15","book":"Deu","chapter":5,"verse":15,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 7:19","book":"Deu","chapter":7,"verse":19,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 8:42","book":"1Ki","chapter":8,"verse":42,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 136:12","book":"Psa","chapter":136,"verse":12,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 32:17","book":"Jer","chapter":32,"verse":17,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 32:21","book":"Jer","chapter":32,"verse":21,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezk 20:33–34","book":"Ezk","chapter":20,"verse":33,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"text","text":" I made the earth, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 45:12","book":"Isa","chapter":45,"verse":12,"letter":"i"},{"kind":"text","text":" and the people, and animals on the face of the earth. I give it to anyone I please. "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":3,"text":"Lit to whomever is upright in my eyes"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 115:15–16","book":"Psa","chapter":115,"verse":15,"letter":"j"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dn 4:17","book":"Dan","chapter":4,"verse":17,"letter":"k"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Dt 4:34","book":"Deu","chapter":4,"verse":34},{"label":"Dt 5:15","book":"Deu","chapter":5,"verse":15},{"label":"Dt 7:19","book":"Deu","chapter":7,"verse":19},{"label":"1Kg 8:42","book":"1Ki","chapter":8,"verse":42},{"label":"Ps 136:12","book":"Psa","chapter":136,"verse":12},{"label":"Jr 32:17","book":"Jer","chapter":32,"verse":17},{"label":"Jr 32:21","book":"Jer","chapter":32,"verse":21},{"label":"Ezk 20:33–34","book":"Ezk","chapter":20,"verse":33},{"label":"Is 45:12","book":"Isa","chapter":45,"verse":12},{"label":"Ps 115:15–16","book":"Psa","chapter":115,"verse":15},{"label":"Dn 4:17","book":"Dan","chapter":4,"verse":17}],"footnotes":[{"marker":3,"text":"Lit to whomever is upright in my eyes"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So now I have placed all these lands under the authority of my servant "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 44:28","book":"Isa","chapter":44,"verse":28,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 25:9","book":"Jer","chapter":25,"verse":9,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" Nebuchadnezzar, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 24:11","book":"2Ki","chapter":24,"verse":11,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 25:22","book":"2Ki","chapter":25,"verse":22,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 36:6–13","book":"2Ch","chapter":36,"verse":6,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" king of Babylon. I have even given him the wild animals to serve him. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 44:28","book":"Isa","chapter":44,"verse":28},{"label":"Jr 25:9","book":"Jer","chapter":25,"verse":9},{"label":"2Kg 24:11","book":"2Ki","chapter":24,"verse":11},{"label":"2Kg 25:22","book":"2Ki","chapter":25,"verse":22},{"label":"2Ch 36:6–13","book":"2Ch","chapter":36,"verse":6}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"All nations will serve him, his son, and his grandson until the time for his own land comes, and then many nations and great kings will enslave him. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 25:12","book":"Jer","chapter":25,"verse":12,"letter":"a"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jr 25:12","book":"Jer","chapter":25,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“ ‘ “As for the nation or kingdom that does not serve King Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon and does not place its neck under the yoke of the king of Babylon, that nation I will punish by sword, famine, and plague —this is the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s declaration —until through him I have destroyed it. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So you should not listen to your prophets, diviners, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 18:10","book":"Deu","chapter":18,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 18:14","book":"Deu","chapter":18,"verse":14,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 14:14","book":"Jer","chapter":14,"verse":14,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 29:8","book":"Jer","chapter":29,"verse":8,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" dreamers, fortune-tellers, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lv 19:26","book":"Lev","chapter":19,"verse":26,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 18:10","book":"Deu","chapter":18,"verse":10,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 18:14","book":"Deu","chapter":18,"verse":14,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 33:6","book":"2Ch","chapter":33,"verse":6,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"text","text":" or sorcerers "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 7:11","book":"Exo","chapter":7,"verse":11,"letter":"i"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 18:10","book":"Deu","chapter":18,"verse":10,"letter":"j"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 33:6","book":"2Ch","chapter":33,"verse":6,"letter":"k"},{"kind":"text","text":" who say to you, ‘Don’t serve the king of Babylon!’ "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Dt 18:10","book":"Deu","chapter":18,"verse":10},{"label":"Dt 18:14","book":"Deu","chapter":18,"verse":14},{"label":"Jr 14:14","book":"Jer","chapter":14,"verse":14},{"label":"Jr 29:8","book":"Jer","chapter":29,"verse":8},{"label":"Lv 19:26","book":"Lev","chapter":19,"verse":26},{"label":"Dt 18:10","book":"Deu","chapter":18,"verse":10},{"label":"Dt 18:14","book":"Deu","chapter":18,"verse":14},{"label":"2Ch 33:6","book":"2Ch","chapter":33,"verse":6},{"label":"Ex 7:11","book":"Exo","chapter":7,"verse":11},{"label":"Dt 18:10","book":"Deu","chapter":18,"verse":10},{"label":"2Ch 33:6","book":"2Ch","chapter":33,"verse":6}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"They are prophesying a lie "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 5:31","book":"Jer","chapter":5,"verse":31,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 14:14","book":"Jer","chapter":14,"verse":14,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 20:6","book":"Jer","chapter":20,"verse":6,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 23:25–26","book":"Jer","chapter":23,"verse":25,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 23:32","book":"Jer","chapter":23,"verse":32,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 27:14–16","book":"Jer","chapter":27,"verse":14,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 29:9","book":"Jer","chapter":29,"verse":9,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 29:21","book":"Jer","chapter":29,"verse":21,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 29:31","book":"Jer","chapter":29,"verse":31,"letter":"i"},{"kind":"text","text":" to you so that you will be removed from your land. I will banish you, and you will perish. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jr 5:31","book":"Jer","chapter":5,"verse":31},{"label":"Jr 14:14","book":"Jer","chapter":14,"verse":14},{"label":"Jr 20:6","book":"Jer","chapter":20,"verse":6},{"label":"Jr 23:25–26","book":"Jer","chapter":23,"verse":25},{"label":"Jr 23:32","book":"Jer","chapter":23,"verse":32},{"label":"Jr 27:14–16","book":"Jer","chapter":27,"verse":14},{"label":"Jr 29:9","book":"Jer","chapter":29,"verse":9},{"label":"Jr 29:21","book":"Jer","chapter":29,"verse":21},{"label":"Jr 29:31","book":"Jer","chapter":29,"verse":31}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But as for the nation that will put its neck under the yoke of the king of Babylon and serve him, I will leave it in its own land, and that nation will cultivate "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit work"},{"kind":"text","text":" it and reside in it. This is the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s declaration.”’”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit work"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I spoke to King Zedekiah of Judah "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 28:1","book":"Jer","chapter":28,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 38:17","book":"Jer","chapter":38,"verse":17,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" in the same way: “Put your necks under the yoke of the king of Babylon, serve him and his people, and live! "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jr 28:1","book":"Jer","chapter":28,"verse":1},{"label":"Jr 38:17","book":"Jer","chapter":38,"verse":17}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Why should you and your people die "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezk 18:31","book":"Ezk","chapter":18,"verse":31,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" by the sword, famine, and plague as the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" has threatened against any nation that does not serve the king of Babylon? "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ezk 18:31","book":"Ezk","chapter":18,"verse":31}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Do not listen to the words of the prophets who are telling you, ‘Don’t serve the king of Babylon,’ for they are prophesying a lie to you. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 14:14","book":"Jer","chapter":14,"verse":14,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jr 14:14","book":"Jer","chapter":14,"verse":14}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"‘I have not sent them’ —this is the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s declaration —‘and they are prophesying falsely in my name; therefore, I will banish you, and you will perish —you and the prophets who are prophesying to you.’”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then I spoke to the priests and all these people, saying, “This is what the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" says: ‘Do not listen to the words of your prophets. They are prophesying to you, claiming, “Look, very soon now the articles of the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s temple will be brought back from Babylon.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 24:13","book":"2Ki","chapter":24,"verse":13,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 36:7","book":"2Ch","chapter":36,"verse":7,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 36:10","book":"2Ch","chapter":36,"verse":10,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 28:3","book":"Jer","chapter":28,"verse":3,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" They are prophesying a lie to you. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 24:13","book":"2Ki","chapter":24,"verse":13},{"label":"2Ch 36:7","book":"2Ch","chapter":36,"verse":7},{"label":"2Ch 36:10","book":"2Ch","chapter":36,"verse":10},{"label":"Jr 28:3","book":"Jer","chapter":28,"verse":3}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Do not listen to them. Serve the king of Babylon and live! Why should this city become a ruin? "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 7:34","book":"Jer","chapter":7,"verse":34,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jr 7:34","book":"Jer","chapter":7,"verse":34}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:18","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"If they are indeed prophets and if the word of the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" is with them, let them intercede with the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" of Armies not to let the articles that remain in the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s temple, in the palace of the king of Judah, and in Jerusalem go to Babylon.’ "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:19","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For this is what the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" of Armies says about the pillars, the basin, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit sea"},{"kind":"text","text":" the water carts, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 25:13","book":"2Ki","chapter":25,"verse":13,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 25:16","book":"2Ki","chapter":25,"verse":16,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 52:17","book":"Jer","chapter":52,"verse":17,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 52:20","book":"Jer","chapter":52,"verse":20,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" and the rest of the articles that still remain in this city, "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 25:13","book":"2Ki","chapter":25,"verse":13},{"label":"2Kg 25:16","book":"2Ki","chapter":25,"verse":16},{"label":"Jr 52:17","book":"Jer","chapter":52,"verse":17},{"label":"Jr 52:20","book":"Jer","chapter":52,"verse":20}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit sea"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:20","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"those King Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon did not take when he deported Jeconiah "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"= Jehoiachin"},{"kind":"text","text":" son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, from Jerusalem to Babylon along with all the nobles of Judah "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 6:17","book":"Neh","chapter":6,"verse":17,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 13:17","book":"Neh","chapter":13,"verse":17,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 39:6","book":"Jer","chapter":39,"verse":6,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" and Jerusalem. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Neh 6:17","book":"Neh","chapter":6,"verse":17},{"label":"Neh 13:17","book":"Neh","chapter":13,"verse":17},{"label":"Jr 39:6","book":"Jer","chapter":39,"verse":6}],"footnotes":[{"marker":2,"text":"= Jehoiachin"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:21","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Yes, this is what the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" of Armies, the God of Israel, says about the articles that remain in the temple of the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the palace of the king of Judah, and in Jerusalem: "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:27:22","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"‘They will be taken to Babylon and will remain there until I attend to them again.’ "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 29:10","book":"Jer","chapter":29,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 32:5","book":"Jer","chapter":32,"verse":5,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" This is the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s declaration. ‘Then I will bring them up and restore them to this place.’” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezr 1:7–11","book":"Ezr","chapter":1,"verse":7,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezr 5:13–15","book":"Ezr","chapter":5,"verse":13,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezr 7:19","book":"Ezr","chapter":7,"verse":19,"letter":"e"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jr 29:10","book":"Jer","chapter":29,"verse":10},{"label":"Jr 32:5","bo